Arabella Advisors is a consulting firm that oversees a major leftwing ‚Äúdark money‚Äù network. Arabella manages the Sixteen Thirty Fund, a 501(c)(4) nonprofit organization that has been widely dubbed as a ‚Äúdark money‚Äù political fund, and its sister project, the New Venture Fund. Other Arabella-managed entities include the Windward Fund and the Hopewell Fund.

Arabella, founded in 2005 by Eric Kessler, an alum of Bill Clinton‚Äôs White House, is known for using its four main funds to prop up paper-thin nonprofit groups that promote left-wing policies. These nonprofits have been dubbed ‚Äúpop-ups‚Äù because most of them appear to be grassroots organizations but, in effect, are barely more than websites. The ‚Äúpop-ups‚Äù drive millions in donations to promote liberal policy issues all while providing cover for whoever is making the donations.

This layer of anonymity has helped Arabella rake in billions into the projects it manages. Between 2013 and 2018, four nonprofits under Arabella‚Äôs umbrella reported a combined revenue of roughly $2.3 billion. Those four funds financed hundreds of leftwing ‚Äúpop-up‚Äù campaigns.

While Arabella‚Äôs projects are often cloaked in secrecy, the organization is facing more scrutiny from corporate media. The Daily Beast reported Arabella got caught scrubbing its Wikipedia pages of mentions of ‚Äúdark money.‚Äù
